title: Jupiter's moon Europa has an ice shell about 18 miles thick — and that could be bad news for alien life
description: Using data gathered by NASA's Juno Jupiter orbiter, scientists estimate that Europa's ice shell is about 18 miles thick — which could make it hard for nutrients to get down to its buried ocean.
